This is one the most exciting and defining moments of my life.
The song "All i need" went straight to #1 on Spotify on its first day and therefore we are releasing the video to our loyal, loved and devoted fans, as promised.
This video is based on the lyrics from the song “All i need”. I wrote the song at a time where our love was challenged by forces beyond our control. I have never doubted my love for my beautiful Jonna, and this song, this video, is a message i want to send to all of you, to never give up on love. 
Thank you all for your support through thick and thin, and for your loyalty. This is just the beginning. You are all we need. / Joakim Lundell

---

To celebrate the happy ending of Noorhelm, I thought it could be fun to do a remake of one of my most popular Noorhelm videos, my first ever AU. I uploaded the original back in early March 2017 with Sony Vegas as editing software. Now four months later I have re-created it in FCP as longer and I used the beautiful acoustic version of All I Need.

Why this version is so special, you ask? 
Because I added EVERY single scene/clip from their story. I'm so happy how it turned out.

I added letterbox aspect ratio 2:35:1 to make it look and feel like a real music video. I want to credit Joakim and his team for the water background, it’s from the real music video of All I Need.

I hope you will enjoy this version of the Swedish youtuber (now also music producer) Joakim Lundell’s song All I Need. Big credit to him for creating this song with the sibling duo Arrhult’s vocals.
___________________________________________________

PLOT/STORY:

Noora and William are together. Their relationship is incredibly strong, but they go through hard times, especially since William have a mental illness. He can without any warnings shut out Noora and people he cares about and get outbreaks and sometimes it goes so far that he hurt people. Noora is very known about she can't do anything, even if she knows what William do is wrong. 

She tries to get in touch and support him during the hard times but he doesn’t accept her support. But when he is okay, he is the best boyfriend Noora could have. Noora will never leave William and he will never leave her because he didn’t choose to be crazy sometimes.

---

NOTE: The story is based on Joakim and his wife Jonna’s own story and it’s what the song really is about, his feelings for Jonna during her times.

CLIP DESCRIPTION:
Navin (Steve Martin) hits rock bottom, leaving Marie (Bernadette Peters) at the house, taking only his chair... and paddle ball game... and lamp...

FILM DESCRIPTION:
Carl Reiner directs Steve Martin (who co-wrote the script with Carl Gottlieb) in this gag-laden comedy about an idiotic white man, raised by a poor family of black sharecroppers, who doesn't realize he's not black. Navin R. Johnson (Steve Martin) is told the horrible truth when he finds himself instinctively tapping his feet to an easy listening tune on the radio, instead of a low-down blues. His mother (Mabel King) tells him he's white and Navin takes to the road (in a World War II bomber helmet and goggles) to start a new life in St. Louis. A filling station owner, Harry Hartounian (Jackie Mason), give Navin his first break, hiring him to pump gas. One day at the station, Navin has a brainstorm, concocting an invention called "The Opti-grab," a combination handle and nose-brace for eyeglasses. But Navin runs into trouble when a crazed killer (M. Emmet Walsh) picks out his name at random from the telephone book and tries to kill him. Navin escapes to a traveling carnival, where he wrangles a job as the "guess-your-weight" man. At the carnival, he discovers his sexual nature, thanks to stunt rider and S&M enthusiast Patty Bernstein (Catlin Adams). But Navin meets the beautiful Marie (Bernadette Peters) and he quickly falls in love. In the meantime, the "Opti-grab" has taken off and soon Navin is a millionaire.
